                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-356-off1865 t18290611-356-crimeloc1867"></join>, looking at the boats; I did not feel my pocket picked - a gentleman told me of it; I then missed my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-356-person2483">
                  GEORGE 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18290611-356-person2483" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-356-person2483" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-356-person2483" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a fisherman. I was pass<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182906110156"></xptr>ing, and saw a number of persons looking through the ballostrades - I saw the prisoner and another push in between the people, and they had the tail of a coat up between them - I saw a handkerchief pass from the coattail into the prisoner's trowsers; I seized him, and took the handkerchief from him - the other got away.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was looking through the rails, and a young man gave me the handkerchief.</p>
